{
  "texts": [
    "GRAG demonstrates strong transferability to transfer learned textual graph encoding capabilities across datasets.",
    "As shown in Table 3, when trained on a large dataset, GRAG can enhance generation on a smaller dataset using the trained model.",
    "Notably, GRAG trained on WebQSP on ExplaGraphs outperforms the naive LLM, with an accuracy improvement of 33.77%.",
    "Larger LLMs don't necessarily outperform smaller ones in graph-related tasks without retrieval.",
    "Beyond the performance comparison of GRAG and RAG models, we evaluated the impact of LLM scale on graph-related tasks, specifically examining the 7B and 13B versions of the Llama model."
  ]
}